message.content:
cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the cylindric semantics of first-order logic and defines a Table/Relation Algebra with operators to translate Horn clauses into algebraic form. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses mechanisms for exporting/importing relations between programs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses relational programming and the role of clauses in Prolog. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses modularity and local scoping of predicates. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of relations as first-class citizens, which is relevant to some areas of AI such as knowledge representation.
